Six Children Die in House Fire in U.S.
WASHINGTON , December 27 ( Xinhua ) -- Six children , the youngest 2 years old , were killed Sunday when a fire sent flames and smoke roaring through the upstairs bedrooms of their grandparents ' home in Detroit , capital of Michigan State of the United States , reports reaching here said .
Three adults and a 10-year-old child escaped , the reports quoted local officials as saying .
The children , aged 2 , 5 , 6 , 7 , 8 and 11 , were found in two bedrooms .
Their mother was not at the home .
Among the adults who escaped was the grandmother .
Two of the adults who escaped were unharmed .
There was no official word on the condition of the two others .
